 Chelsea on Wednesday beat Krasnodar 4-0 in their second match of the UEFA Champions League this season. Callum Hudson-Odoi scored the first for the Blues in the 37th minute, with Timo Wener scoring the second from the penalty spot, 76 minutes into the game. New signing Hakim Ziyech got his name on the score sheet for the first time for the London club, three minutes later, and Christian Pulisic rounded up the victory for Chelsea in 90 minutes. Jorginho missed a penalty for Chelsea earlier in the match. The Blues next face Rennes in Stamford Bridge next Wednesday.  Details Shortlyâ€¦..